broken-main session (an unrelated automation fix carried the unblock).

**Verification:** verified-local ‚Äî the annotation fix made `pixi run mypy` pass
locally (`Success: no issues found in 411 source files`) and the commit's
pre-commit mypy hook passed; the carrying PR #1568's full CI was still pending at
capture time. Honestly NOT verified-ci.

### What changed
- Added a NEW finding under the same `pass_filenames: false` whole-tree mypy
  variant: a just-merged PR (#1566, a test-suite reorganization) left missing
  type annotations on dict/list literals (`results = {"benchmarks": []}`,
  `improvements = []`, etc.) that mypy flags as `Need type annotation for "X"
  [var-annotated]`. Because lint is SKIPPED on auto-merge events in this repo,
  the broken code reached main; the NEXT PR author's unrelated commit is the one
  that surfaces all 10 errors (all in `tests/unit/benchmarks/test_compare.py`, a
  file that branch never touched).
- Added the fix detail: explicit annotations matching the target signatures in
  `hephaestus/benchmarks/compare.py` ‚Äî
  `results: dict[str, Any] = {...}`,
  `improvements: list[dict[str, Any]] = []`,
  `regressions: list[Regression] = []`, plus `from typing import Any`.
- Documented the IN-PR-FOLD decision: the unblock fix was FOLDED INTO the
  unrelated feature PR (#1568) because there was no other way to make that PR's
  own commit pass the whole-tree hook ‚Äî fixing broken main is a prerequisite for
  ANY other PR landing. Noted the alternative (a tiny standalone unblock PR
  first) and that you should state which you did and why.
- Added a "confirm errors pre-exist on origin/main" diagnostic step
  (`git show origin/main:<file>` / `git diff --name-only main...HEAD`) before
  assuming your change caused them.
- Added a related-discovery note: a test-suite reorg (#1566) MOVED files ‚Äî
  `tests/unit/test_import_surface.py` / `test_automation_boundary.py` are now
  under `tests/unit/validation/`. Passing a now-nonexistent test path to pytest
  collects nothing and EXITS 0 (silent no-op) ‚Äî always confirm a targeted pytest
  path matched tests (look for the "N passed" line, not just exit 0).
- Added two Failed Attempts rows, one new "When to Use" trigger, a cross-link to
  [[ci-markdownlint-all-files-repo-wide-blocks-prs]], and a "Verified On" row.
  Bumped Overview to "three variants (two mypy findings)" and date to 2026-06-22.

### Why
The same diagnostic signature recurred ("mypy fails on a file I never touched;
empty diff vs origin/main") but with a DIFFERENT mypy error class than v1.2.0's
version-bump `[method-assign]`/re-export errors: here a freshly-MERGED PR (#1566)
introduced `[var-annotated]` errors that "lint skipped on auto-merge" let slip
onto main. The fix is the same root pattern (unblock broken main first), but this
session chose to FOLD the unblock into the carrying PR #1568 rather than ship a
standalone prereq PR ‚Äî the only way to make that PR's own commit pass the
whole-tree gate. Captured the fold-vs-standalone tradeoff explicitly, the
auto-merge-skips-lint mechanism, and the pytest silent-no-op-on-moved-paths
gotcha so future authors confirm pre-existence and watch for "N passed".

