the broader root cause: any whole-dir / repo-wide pre-commit hook configured
with `pass_filenames: false` will re-run over the ENTIRE tree on every commit,
so a pre-existing violation already committed on `origin/main` aborts unrelated
commits on every branch. Added the `ruff check` lint-violation variant
(`SIM102` "Use a single if statement instead of nested if statements"
committed on main via PR #1346 at HEAD `580ab43`, in
